    description: "Tri-County Christian is a small body of believers united in Christ desiring to LIVE biblically and BE LIKE Jesus in all aspects of our lives.\n\nOur prayer is that every person entering our doors on Sunday (or any day of the week) will be encouraged, and leave having truly worshipped in Spirit and Truth. (John 4:23)\n\nElements of our worship include:\n\nMUSIC: Scripture commands us to sing! (Colossians 3:16) Our prayer is, that as we sing God is adored by our church family worshipping Him through song.\n\nCOMMUNION: We follow the example given by the early church, where they met weekly for the purpose of remembering Christ’s death on the cross. (Acts 2:42)\n\nPREACHING: God’s Word is absolute truth. We pray that God’s Word and the Holy Spirit will move each of us into a deeper relationship with God as we live more and more like Jesus everyday. (Hebrews 4:12)\n\nTITHES AND OFFERINGS: We pass the plate each week, not only to share in the work of building God’s Kingdom financially, but also as a reminder that we share in this work with our time, talents and resources that God has blessed us with. (Malachi 3:10)\n\nPRAYER: Jesus taught us how to pray and there are many example in the bible of the power of prayer. We come together each week to pray for one another through the joys and sorrows. (James 5:14-16)",
