    description: "**﻿﻿Job Title:** Worship Minister\n\n**Purpose Statement:** As an employee of FBC Portland, this position represents this ministry publicly and privately. As a result, this position is expected to live a life that is Gospel centered and glorifies Jesus Christ. Each full-time, part-time or temporary employee is expected to affirm FBC Portland’s Statement of Faith, Core Values, Doctrinal Distinctives and Christian Code of Conduct laid out in FBC’s By-laws and in the Personnel Policies & Procedures Manual.\n\n**Position Summary:** The Worship Minister is a part-time position and is not benefits eligible. This position will be responsible for working with the Senior Pastor to select songs – based on Scripture – which lead the congregation in meaningful worship of God. The Worship Minister will lead and mentor musicians, vocalists and other volunteers including video, sound, and lighting. The candidate should possess a heart for leading a congregation in worship and thrive working in a team environment.\n\n**Reports to:** Senior Pastor\n\n**Job Duties and Responsibilities:**\n\n1. Oversee Worship & Creative Arts for Sunday morning services, and occasional special services.\n\n2. Primary Worship Leader and Chief Musician\n\n- Work alongside Senior Pastor for teaching schedule, themes, direction, and creative elements.\n- Partner with Senior Pastor in developing the order of service for the upcoming Sunday morning schedule.\n- Play a musical instrument [e.g., guitar, piano] and sing during worship ",
