    description: "**Position: Pastor**\n\n**Non-Denominational**\n\n**Weekly Attendance: 35**\n\n**Bonsall Community Church**\n\n**Bonsall, California 92003**\n\n**About the Pastor**\n\nThe pastor of our church will most likely be a bi-vocational pastor, leading and overseeing the preaching and teaching ministry. The church expects dedicated time to study, to reflect, and prepare for delivering God's Word. The Pastor is considered a Teaching Elder and is a member of the church Elder Board. The Elders guide the congregation in making good, biblical, decisions and guidance for Christ’s church. The Pastor encourages spiritual growth within the church and works to create a church environment that helps all members apply biblical teaching to their daily lives. The Pastor offers pastoral care and guidance during key life moments and helps develop ministries that foster spiritual growth and support the broader God given mission of the church.\n\nThrough his leadership, teaching, and example, the Pastor helps shape a congregation grounded in biblical principles, making a meaningful impact in the community and beyond.\n\n**The Pastor’s responsibilities**\n\nThe Pastor serves as the primary spiritual leader of the church, providing vision, biblical leadership, and relational care while equipping the congregation to grow in faith and mission. The Pastor provides clear, compelling biblical preaching and teaching, grounded in a deep knowledge of Scriptures and a firm commitment to the inerrancy and authority of God's Word. ",
