    employmentType: "FULL_TIME",
    description: "The Children’s Ministry Director is responsible for executing our mission with the next generation. You are not just managing a ministry; you are leading a movement to reach families who are disconnected from God and helping them discover the full life Jesus promised. You lead the team that aims to ensure every child that walks through our doors knows we are **For them** because Jesus is **For them**.\n\n**The essential job functions include, but are not limited to the following:**\n\nLeadership & Team Oversight\n\n**Cast Vision** for the Christ’s Kids team through intentional and consistent discipleship, ensuring each volunteer, leader, and coach understands the \"why\" behind the \"what.\"\n\n**Provide direct supervision,** leadership and accountability for Christ’s Kids Preschool Director, Children’s Ministry Assistant and key ministry leads.\n\nVision Alignment\n\n**For Jesus:** Ensure that every environment we create points kids toward a relationship with Christ. This means prioritizing biblical accuracy, keeping the Gospel at the center of our teaching, and helping children understand how to live out their faith in their daily lives.\n\n**For Each Other:** Oversee a \"Leadership Pipeline\" where volunteers are personally known and spiritually fed. You are responsible for the spiritual health of the Christ's Kids volunteer community.\n\n**For Camden:** Oversee high-visibility community bridges like **Connect Camps** and **Preschool integration**, ensuring we show compassion and dignity to eve",
